<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Star_of_David&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>In <a href="/wiki/Unicode" title="Unicode">Unicode</a>, the "Star of David" symbol is U+2721 (<font size="+3"><span class="Unicode">✡</span></font>).</li>
<li>The world's largest star (167 m = 547.9 feet diameter) is in the <a href="/w/index.php?title=Smokey_Hills_Weapons_Range&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Smokey Hills Weapons Range (page does not exist)">Smokey Hills Weapons Range</a>, <a href="/wiki/Kansas" title="Kansas">Kansas</a>, USA <span class="plainlinksneverexpand"><a href="http://stable.toolserver.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Star_of_David&amp;params=38.717704_N_97.80673_W_" class="external text" title="http://stable.toolserver.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Star_of_David&amp;params=38.717704_N_97.80673_W_" rel="nofollow"><span class="geo-nondefault"><span class="geo-dms" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location"><span class="latitude">38°43′04″N</span> <span class="longitude">97°48′24″W</span></span></span><span class="geo-multi-punct">﻿ / ﻿</span><span class="geo-default"><span class="geo-dec" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location">38.717704°N 97.80673°W</span><span style="display:none">﻿ / <span class="geo">38.717704; -97.80673</span></span></span></a></span></li>
</ul>
